==Irish==

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[ˈiːnʲə]}}

===Etymology===
[[Old Irish]] ''[[aíne]]'' < [[Latin]] ''[[ieiunum]]'' "fast" (because Fridays were originally days for fasting in Roman Catholicism)

===Noun===
'''Aoine''' ''f'' ([[plural|pl.]] [[Aointe]])

# [[Friday]]

